CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, November 5, 1955, pg. 1B reads: "Prime Minister tells newspaper, men at dinner in Press Club of his experiences in Pittsburgh twenty-eight years ago and of his plans for making Nigeria an independent, self-sufficient nation."
TitMainTitle: Eastern Nigerian Prime Minister Nnamdi Azikiwe wearing agbada and cap, standing at head of banquet table speaking to group of men, including P. L. Prattis, Earl Hord, Beverly Carter, and Bill Nunn Sr. seated on right, in Press Club, another version
